			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerTitleCompanyLabel">Director of External Production, Sony Computer Entertainment America</span></td>
		        </tr>
		        <tr>
			        <td valign="top" class="tableCell"><span id="speakerBioLabel">In 1991, John built his first game, Battleship, and acquired the rights from Milton-Bradley to create videogame versions of popular board games for the Philips CDi player. Since that time he has worked on over 25 games and 9 edutainment products.

Prior to joining Sony, John held management and creative positions with Atari, Electronic Arts, Westwood Studios, and 3DO. In his role as Executive Producer and Director of Design for Electronic Arts, John contributed to the design and production of Nox, Command & Conquer: Red Alert 2, and Yuri’s Revenge.

Hight oversees three business units for Sony: External Production, Localization, and e-Distribution. Recent game releases include Tourist Trophy, and Shadow of the Colossus. The e-Distribution Initiative is a newly announced downloadable content service for the PlayStation 3. 

John holds a B.S.E. in Computer Science from the University of New Mexico and an M.B.A. from U.S.C.’s Marshall School of Business. He is also authoring a project management book in the Game Design Essentials series by Thomson Delmar.
</span></td>
